Rodong Sinmun on Faith in Independence 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, December 20 (KCNA) -- Faith in independence has made DPRK display its imposing sight as an ever-victorious powerful state and its people grow as a heroic people carving out the new era of history in the van, declares Rodong Sinmun in an editorial article Wednesday, a summary of which reads: 
 Faith in independence is the best weapon for the prosperity of the country. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It is the main factor on which depend the ups and downs of a country and a nation. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The greatest wealth and asset of the prosperity of the country is faith in independence. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Only a people strong in this faith can add shine to the honor and dignity of the country and hew a true road of national prosperity.  &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Faith in independence is a powerful weapon to defend the dignity and rights of the nation.  &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It is immediately the dignity and authority of the nation.  &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Faith in independence is the mental source in bringing up the army and the people into indomitable fighters. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The people of the DPRK are a dignified people who have grown strong with firm faith in themselves. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Faith in independence is an asset guaranteeing the constant development of the national economy.  &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 An economy suitable to the country's conditions and serving its own people is one built with faith in independence.  &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The building of the national economy based on faith in independence is a true path of prosperity and leap. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The army and people of the DPRK are strong-willed heroic ones who treasure the spirit of national independence as their own lives. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Their faith in independence is unshakable ideological sentiments based on the conviction of the justice of the cause of the Songun revolution of the Workers' Party of Korea. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Underlying their strong spirit of independence is the rock-firm conviction of the victory of the Party's cause of Songun revolution.  &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Songun is, so to speak, dignity, sovereignty and right to existence. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The conviction of the victory of the cause of Songun revolution cherished by the army and people of the DPRK today is immediately unquestioned trust in leader Kim Jong Il, the peerlessly brilliant commander of Songun. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Their faith in independence is an invincible spiritual strength based on the most solid unity of the army and the people. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Their single-minded unity forged in the protracted struggle for national independence and lifted to a new, higher stage in the flames of the Songun revolution is the invincible treasured sword of Songun Korea stronger than a nuclear weapon and a fundamental source of the independent spirit of the people. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Their faith in independence is noble ideological sentiments spurting from the national pride in the great power of the state. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 This power is a firm guarantee for defense of the country's sovereignty and national prosperity. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It is the unanimous desire and will of the army and people of the DPRK to glorify the height of prosperity of the country by rushing forward like the wind with faith in independence and burning patriotic zeal.   &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The army and people of the DPRK should stir up themselves once again as they have brought happiness by pulling through manifold difficulties in the revolutionary spirit of self-reliance and hard struggle and display the mettle of the nation to the world and make a leaping progress like the wind towards the peak of a great prosperous powerful nation. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 They should struggle with the Juche idea and Songun idea as the eternal guideline of life and fight.   &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 They should establish the monolithic system of leadership of the headquarters of the revolution more thoroughly in the whole party, army and society and consolidate army-people unity based on the Songun idea in every way. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 They should treasure the precious gains of the revolution and give full scope to the superiority of the nation. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 They should turn out as one man in the general march for the prosperity of the country with the ardent zeal of patriotism. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 They should display the honor and pride of the DPRK citizens with great ability.   &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 An endless bright future has been unfolded before the army and the people of the DPRK today.

DPRK's Important Days Celebrated in Different Countries 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, December 20 (KCNA) -- Round-table talks and lectures took place in Laos and Indonesia and a book and photo exhibition and film show in Austria on Dec. 12 and 13 respectively on the occasions the 15th anniversary of Kim Jong Il's assumption of the supreme commandership of the Korean People's Army and the 89th birth anniversary of anti-Japanese war hero Kim Jong Suk.
 On display in the venues of the events were works of President Kim Il Sung and Kim Jong Il and other Korean books and photos showing the Songun leadership feats performed by him. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The secretary of the Vientiane City Committee of the Lao People's Revolutionary Youth Union at round-table talks noted that the Lao youths know well about the Songun revolutionary leadership feats of Kim Jong Il and the revolutionary career of Kim Jong Suk, stressing the need to develop the relations between the youth organizations of the two countries. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Harn Sinuraya, general director of Rabitra Bahtera Pratama Co. of Indonesia, said after listening to the lecture that Kim Jong Suk was a great woman who safeguarded the President in every hard-fought battle at the risk of her life and gave birth to Kim Jong Il and brought him up as a successor to the revolution, adding that he is now working world-startling miracles one after another as he grew up under such care. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Adolf Pilz, chairman of the Society for the Promotion of the Relations between Austria and DPRK, addressing the book and photo exhibition, noted that he would strive hard to develop the bilateral ties of friendship and cooperation. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The participants of the film show watched Korean film "The respected Comrade Kim Jong Il is a great thinker and theoretician."

Songun Idea and Policy Studied in Different Countries 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, December 20 (KCNA) -- The Songun idea and policy have been studied and introduced in more than 120 countries and regions including Russia, Syria, India, Belarus, France and Uganda this year.
 Kim Jong Il's famous works on the Juche idea, the basis of the Songun idea, were brought out in booklet by organizations and institutions of over 40 countries including the Mongolia Mt. Paektu Association for Independent Development and the Futra Publishing House of the Czech Republic. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Political parties and organizations in Nepal, Pakistan, Italy, Democratic Congo and many other countries published books and bulletins explaining the principle and originality of the Songun idea founded and enriched by President Kim Il Sung and Kim Jong Il and praising the might of the DPRK. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Such events as seminars, lectures and round-table talks were held on over 500 occasions, with an attendance of political and social figures and broad sections of people. The participants stressed that the Songun idea and policy serves as a guarantee for defending the sovereignty and prosperity of each country and nation and ensuring global peace and security. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The East European and Central Asian Regional Association for the Study of the Juche Idea and the Songun Policy described the Songun policy pursued by Kim Jong Il as the greatest policy in the present era and adopted a declaration calling for following the policy. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 In the meantime, at least 300 media bodies of the world gave publicity to the might and vitality of the Songun idea and policy. Among them were the Russian newspaper Patriot, Prensa Latina news agency of Cuba, the Lao newspaper Pasason and the Bulgarian newspaper Duma.

Military Attaches Corps Visits Panmunjom 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, December 20 (KCNA) -- The military attaches corps in Pyongyang visited Panmunjom on Dec. 19 on the occasion of the 15th anniversary of Kim Jong Il's assumption of supreme commandership of the Korean People's Army.
 The guests saw the monument bearing autography of President Kim Il Sung showing his immortal exploits in the noble cause of national reunification. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 They were briefed on the brilliant victory the army and the people of the DPRK won by smashing the armed invasion of the imperialist allied forces in the Fatherland Liberation War under the wise leadership of the President before making a round of the meeting room of armistice talks, the hall where the armistice agreement was signed and the former meeting room of the Military Armistice Commission. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Yang Xilian, military attache of the Chinese embassy who is doyen of the corps, wrote in the visitor's book that the Korean Peninsula would surely be reunified in the near future. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Igor Pablov, military attache of the Russian embassy, wrote in the visitor's book that he believed the U.S. forces would be withdrawn from the Korean Peninsula and Korea be reunified at an early date. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Earlier, the members of the corps drove to the post of Mt. Taedok and went round different places before conversing with soldiers there.

War Moves of U.S. and S. Korean Authorities against DPRK Blasted 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, December 20 (KCNA) -- The United States and south Korean bellicose forces are said to have recently agreed upon rounding off by the end of next year "CONPLAN 5029" targeted against the DPRK through the Joint Chiefs of Staff of the south Korean army and the "South Korea-U.S. Combined Forces Command" according to the strategic guideline adopted at the 38th South Korea-U.S. annual security consultative meeting which was held in October. 
 It must not go unnoticed that they are planning to stage a massive war game against the DPRK with the completion of the "CONPLAN 5029". &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Commenting on this, a Rodong Sinmun analyst Wednesday says: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The United States is trying to pull a dirty business against the DPRK behind the curtain of talks. This is clear proof that it is seeking to vanquish the DPRK with a military strong arm, whetting its sword of aggression under the mask of dialogue. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It is a mistake if the U.S. thinks it can bludgeon the DPRK into submission with the double-dealing tactics which it has employed for decades. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The Bush group is still clinging to its trite hostile policy toward the DPRK, remaining captive to the anachronistic way of thinking. This is only driving the present situation to a more serious phase. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Watching the acts of the U.S. bellicose forces framing war plots against the DPRK behind the scene while holding dialogue under the public eyes, the DPRK is getting further convinced that the United States is a dangerous one incredible as ever. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 We have a few words of warning to the south Korean bellicose forces. For them to dance to the drum-beating of the U.S. war-thirsty elements watching for a chance of a new war against the DPRK is an act of bringing a war to the Korean Peninsula. This is an indelible crime in the history of the nation &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The DPRK will decisively smash the vicious challenge of the enemies with the might of Songun.

Ostrich Farm in DPRK 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, December 20 (KCNA) -- Ostrich is being bred in a scientific and technical way in the Democratic People's Republic of Korea.
 There is an ostrich farm in a suburb of Pyongyang, which started its operation in September Juche 89 (2000). &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 According to Chief Engineer of the farm Kim Yong Bin, the farm has recently built a computer database for establishing the ostrich breeding system and confirmed various scientific and technical issues such as the norm of nutritious substances for ostriches according to phases of their growth. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It has also successfully solved the fodder issue in the winter season by treating dry grass with microorganism. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Meanwhile, it is doing well the veterinary and anti-epizootic work by self-producing chicken plague vaccine for ostriches and ordinary veterinary medicines. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The farm has an ostrich breeding cage, young ostrich cage, hatchery and other buildings. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The roof of the ostrich fattening cage is made in a scientific calculation of sunshine. It makes it possible to safely breed ostriches even in the cold winter. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Each cage was designed on the basis of scientific calculation and new construction methods so as to fully meet the ecological demand of the ostrich including supply of fodder and water. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It has also a workshop furnished with all facilities from slaughtering to meat processing.

A Bird Flies to Pyongyang from Moscow
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, December 20 (KCNA) -- A bird with an identification ring attached to its left leg was caught at the foot of a hill in Pyongyang, attracting experts' attention.
 The bird, which is called Emberiza Spodocephala Pallas, wears a ring with the letters "XN 44459" and "Moscow".&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 As soon as an avian fan caught it, he informed the Central Committee of the DPRK Natural Conservation Union about it. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It is distributed in the northeast area of China, Siberia of Russia and Japanese islands. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 In the light of regional connection, there is a view that it can propagate itself in Korea, too. And it is told that some people saw the bird in highland areas. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 However, it is the first time that the bird was found in woods of Pyongyang. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The fact that the bird came from Moscow to Pyongyang makes it possible to clarify the migrant route, period and habitats of the bird in a scientific way.  In particular, today when the bird flu is spread by migrants, it is of very importance to study birds and exchange the information each other. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The Central Committee of the Natural Conservation Union and related units of the DPRK are now deepening study on the bird in contact with relevant institutions of Russia.

Talks between Delegations of SPA of DPRK and State Great Hural of Mongolia
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, December 20 (KCNA) -- Talks between a delegation of the Supreme People's Assembly of the DPRK and a delegation of the State Great Hural of Mongolia took place at the Mansudae Assembly Hall today. 
 Present at the talks were deputies to the SPA Kim Wan Su, chairman of the Korea-Mongolia Friendship Parliamentary Group, Pak Gyu Hong and officials concerned from the DPRK side and members of the delegation of the State Great Hural of Mongolia headed by R. Badamdamdin, chairman of the Mongolia-Korea Friendship Parliamentary Group, and Janchivdorjyn Lomvo, Mongolian ambassador to the DPRK from the Mongolian side. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The two sides at the talks exchanged views on the issue of boosting the relations between the SPA and the State Great Hural of Mongolia and a series of issues of common concern.  &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The talks proceeded in a friendly atmosphere.
